        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add agent-sandbox provider",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add a Kubernetes Agent Sandbox provider with warmup, run, list, status, stop, cleanup, and doctor support\n- target the official Agent Sandbox `v0.5.0rc1` `v1beta1` API through the operator's existing `kubectl`\n- archive-sync repositories and stream commands through Kubernetes exec while validating claim ownership, scope, UID, lifecycle, and pinned container identity\n- enforce lease TTL through `shutdownTime` with `shutdownPolicy: Retain`, terminal expiry handling, and exact retained-claim cleanup\n- add provider docs, metadata, configuration coverage, regression tests, and an opt-in live smoke test with replacement-sync verification\n\nCloses https://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/issues/321\n\n## Dependency cost\n- no `go.mod`, `go.sum`, Worker package, or lockfile changes\n- no Kubernetes Go SDK dependency; Crabbox invokes the operator's configured `kubectl`\n- final Darwin arm64 CLI growth versus `origin/main`: 535,856 bytes (0.410%)\n\n## Security and lifecycle hardening\n- reject unsafe kubeconfig paths and option-like Kubernetes identities before constructing kubectl argv\n- pin claim UID, provider scope, recovery nonce, local expiry, and selected container before subsequent execution or deletion\n- reconcile ambiguous creates only when the exact recovery identity can be proven\n- stage archive replacement inside the mounted workdir, preserve rollback data on failure, and avoid requiring a writable parent directory\n- fail closed on missing, replaced, expired, or ownership-mismatched claims\n- preserve explicit `execTimeoutSecs: 0` as no provider command deadline rather than silently restoring the default\n\n## Verification\nExact reviewed and live-tested head: `2c7dd21fb0cad4853b114491af9db885aca551cd`\n\n- `go build -trimpath -o bin/crabbox ./cmd/crabbox`\n- `go vet ./...`\n- `go test -race ./...`\n- `node --test scripts/*.test.js` (235 passed)\n- `npm run format:check --prefix worker`\n- `npm run lint --prefix worker`\n- `npm run check --prefix worker`\n- `npm test --prefix worker` (22 files, 604 tests)\n- `npm run build --prefix worker`\n- `scripts/check-docs.sh` (48 command docs, 56 providers, 179 links)\n- `node --test scripts/live-agent-sandbox-smoke.test.js` (6 passed)\n- `git diff --check`\n- repository autoreview: accepted and fixed zero-timeout semantics finding; rerun clean with no actionable findings\n\n## Live end-to-end proof\nValidated on a fresh local kind cluster running the official `registry.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/agent-sandbox-controller:v0.5.0rc1` controller.\n\n- exact-head lifecycle smoke passed on `2c7dd21f`: warmup, initial sync/run, retained-lease rerun, replacement sync deleting a stale remote-only file, status, and stop\n- adversarial lifecycle passed: implicit container pinning survived a malicious default-container annotation change; claim-scope tampering blocked both run and cleanup; remote exit code 42 was preserved; exact stop removed the claim\n- TTL lifecycle passed: `shutdownPolicy: Retain`, controller `ClaimExpired`/`SandboxExpired`, retained root claim with the same UID, deleted sandbox and pod, CLI `state=expired`, then exact stop with zero remaining claims\n- post-run cluster state: zero Crabbox Agent Sandbox claims\n\n## Browser verification\nBuilt the docs site and inspected `/providers/agent-sandbox.html` in Chrome. The rendered page documents `v0.5.0rc1`, retained TTL semantics, mounted-workdir staging, terminal expiry handling, replacement-sync live testing, and zero-timeout behavior, with no horizontal overflow at a 1166px viewport.\n",
